loadFromFile(File) - Static method in class org.sd.text.MultiTermFinder
Load a MultiTermFinder from a definition file with the following format: Blank lines and lines beginning with '#' are ignored as formatting and comments. Lines beginning with '%' contain a logical expression string (after the %). Lines beginning with '$' contain [caseSensitive] and [matchFlag] (space delimited) to begin definition of a term finder as referenced by logical expression(s) and are followed by lines with comma-delimited terms (ignoring blank lines and comments) and/or lines beginning with '@' which reference a file with terms to load. All terms are considered to be included in a term finder until another '$' or EOF is encountered.

loadSettings(File) - Static method in class org.sd.crawl.SearchEngineSettings
Load a search engine settings file with fields of the form: name | queryPrefix | queryPostfix | resultLinkKey | nextResultsPageKey Where name -- is the name and key for the setting. queryPrefix -- is the constant portion of a query url before a query's text. queryPostfix -- is the constant portion of a query url after a query's text. resultLinkKey -- is the (sd) xPath to identify result (hit) links from the search engine. nextResutlsPageKey -- is the (sd) xPath to identify getting the "next" page of results from the search engine. lowContentBrNum -- is the number of the br node in the content at which the body text starts. highContentBrNum -- is the number of the br node in the content at which the body text ends. Note that blank lines and lines beginning with '#' are ignored.
